 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definitions of the class of assembly features and how these structures relate to product data, but does not include detailed definition of items of features. 
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li>specification of the use of a characterized object as an assembly feature definition of a product;</li>
<li>specification of the use of a shape aspect as a instanced assembly feature of a product;</li>
<li>specification of the shape aspect relationship as an peer-to-peer relationship between a pair of instanced assembly feature.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>detailed definition and representation of assembly feature definition and instanced assembly features.</li>
 </outscope>

